# ff3ae2390a8c4674a1d3c95964aec4d5
#: ../../developer-guide/plugins/example-plugins/query-remap/example-query-remap.en.rst:21
msgid "Example: Query Remap Plugin"
msgstr ""

# 2072f6f54c4d4a2f8200adceb328edd0
#: ../../developer-guide/plugins/example-plugins/query-remap/example-query-remap.en.rst:23
msgid ""
"The sample remap plugin, ``query_remap.c``, maps client requests to a "
"number of servers based on a hash of the request's URL query parameter. "
"This can be useful for spreading load for a given type of request among "
"backend servers, while still maintaining \"stickiness\" to a single "
"server for similar requests. For example, a search engine may want to "
"send repeated queries for the same keywords to a server that has likely "
"cached the result from a prior query."
msgstr ""

# 4641cc81b0f34e369b82cae91324f335
#: ../../developer-guide/plugins/example-plugins/query-remap/example-query-remap.en.rst:32
msgid "Configuration of query\\_remap"
msgstr ""

# d5f0c35d180f4e66a38358f85d14d6cd
#: ../../developer-guide/plugins/example-plugins/query-remap/example-query-remap.en.rst:34
msgid ""
"The query remap plugin will allow the query parameter name to be "
"specified, along with the hostnames of the servers to hash across. Sample"
" ``remap.config`` rules using ``query_remap`` will look like:"
msgstr ""

# 56db32c641244302902f3cdbcfb9fe2d
#: ../../developer-guide/plugins/example-plugins/query-remap/example-query-remap.en.rst:43
msgid ""
"The first ``@pparam`` specifies the query param key for which the value "
"will be hashed. The remaining parameters list the hostnames of the "
"servers. A request for ``http://www.example.com/search?q=apache`` will "
"match the first rule. The plugin will look for the *``q``* parameter and "
"hash the value '``apache``\\ ' to pick from among "
"``srch_[1-3]_.example.com`` to send the request."
msgstr ""

# e844c204001f4c98833f71c678018fbf
#: ../../developer-guide/plugins/example-plugins/query-remap/example-query-remap.en.rst:50
msgid ""
"If the request does not include a *``q``* query parameter and the plugin "
"decides not to modify the request, the default toURL "
"'``http://srch1.example.com/search``\\ ' will be used by TS."
msgstr ""

# 137a7ab7d6f94f97901a317a02614ade
#: ../../developer-guide/plugins/example-plugins/query-remap/example-query-remap.en.rst:54
msgid ""
"The parameters are passed to the plugin's ``tsremap_new_instance`` "
"function. In ``query_remap``, ``tsremap_new_instance`` creates a plugin-"
"defined ``query_remap_info`` struct to store its configuration "
"parameters. The ihandle, an opaque pointer that can be used to pass per-"
"instance data, is set to this struct pointer and will be passed to the "
"``tsremap_remap`` function when it is triggered for a request."
msgstr ""

# b66a15e48e6a4d13a84edd00d6165fb7
#: ../../developer-guide/plugins/example-plugins/query-remap/example-query-remap.en.rst:88
msgid ""
"Another way remap plugins may want handle more complex configuration is "
"to specify a configuration filename as a ``pparam`` and parse the "
"specified file during instance initialization."
msgstr ""

# 25825b220fd04529b8b367bb20d92bd0
#: ../../developer-guide/plugins/example-plugins/query-remap/example-query-remap.en.rst:93
msgid "Performing the Remap"
msgstr ""

# 3e9500c12cab423ea612f23cd8412700
#: ../../developer-guide/plugins/example-plugins/query-remap/example-query-remap.en.rst:95
msgid ""
"The plugin implements the ``tsremap_remap`` function, which is called "
"when TS has read the client HTTP request headers and matched the request "
"to a remap rule configured for the plugin. The ``TSRemapRequestInfo`` "
"struct contains input and output members for the remap operation."
msgstr ""

# 80a7f11157e84d1c81f538f75cd67403
#: ../../developer-guide/plugins/example-plugins/query-remap/example-query-remap.en.rst:100
msgid ""
"``tsremap_remap`` uses the configuration information passed via the "
"``ihandle`` and checks the ``request_query`` for the configured query "
"parameter. If the parameter is found, the plugin sets a ``new_host`` to "
"modify the request host:"
msgstr ""

